response.original_title: Great Stories of the Great Lakes
response.overview: The history of the Great Lakes is filled with interesting stories about tragic shipwrecks, brave crewmen battling crippling storms, haunted lighthouses, and dramatic rescues. Includes accounts of such famous shipwrecks as: the Edmund Fitzgerald, the Eastland, the Cedarville, and the Rouse Simmons.
response.title: Great Stories of the Great Lakes
